org.janusgraph.graphdb.transaction.subquerycache

Interface SubqueryCache

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    EmptySubqueryCache, GuavaSubqueryCache, SubsetSubqueryCache

    public interface SubqueryCache
    Cache for JointIndexQuery.Subquery results. Cache entries are manually added using get(JointIndexQuery.Subquery, Callable) or put(JointIndexQuery.Subquery, List), and stored in the cache until evicted or invalidated.
    Author:
    Boxuan Li (liboxuan@connect.hku.hk)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

    • Method Detail

      • getIfPresent

        List<Object> getIfPresent(JointIndexQuery.Subquery query)
        Return a list of results if given query exists in cache, otherwise return null
        Parameters:
        query - a subquery of joint index query
        Returns:
        a list of matching results or null if is not in the cache

      • put

        void put(JointIndexQuery.Subquery query,
         List<Object> values)
        Add given values into cache
        Parameters:
        query - a subquery of joint index query
        values - a list of results to be cached

      • get

        List<Object> get(JointIndexQuery.Subquery query,
                 Callable<? extends List<Object>> valueLoader)
          throws Exception
        Returns a list of results. If given query not in cache, call the value loader to retrieve results and put into the cache
        Parameters:
        query - a subquery of joint index query
        valueLoader - a callable that returns a list of results
        Returns:
        a list of results
        Throws:
        Exception - if exception thrown when calling the value loader

      • close

        void close()
        Closes the cache which allows the cache to release allocated memory. Calling any of the other methods after closing a cache has undetermined behavior.
